e to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">develop an environmental impact assessment for CCS in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> the marine environment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Dr Jerry Blackfor</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">d of PML is the UK CCS Research Area Champion for Ecosystems and Environmental Impact and also provides advice to UK governmental departments and international organizations, industry and NGOs on issues related to climate change and CCS.  Dr Steve Widdicom</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">be of PML has provided evidence on the ecological implications associated with geological storage of CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> to the London Convention.  PML also</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> communicate</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> its findings to a wide range of different stakeholders</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> has produced a glossary of terms </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">“t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">he L</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">anguage of CCS</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">” </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">as part of a European project</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, which the Committee might find useful and is available for download at</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><a href="http://www.eco2-project.eu/info